<TEXTAREA NAME="Text" COLS="60" ROWS="6" WRAP="VIRTUAL">&gt; Ok, I think that if the Sonic Team isn't going to put this sort of a section up, I guess I'll have to...
&gt; 
&gt; 1.  Knuckles/Rouge &quot;Mystery&quot; Move
&gt; 
&gt;       For Rouge it's called the SCREW KICK.  This allows you to jump higher than you usually do.  Both are similar, and can be performed by rotating the analog stick and pressing B.  Here are two examples for what it is used for:
&gt; 
&gt;         a. Getting that extra life in Dry Lagoon
&gt;         b. Getting that emerald in Mad Space(near the top)
&gt; 
&gt; 2.  Live Ammunition
&gt; 
&gt;       This concerns Omochao.  If you think you know, don't read on.  Omochao can be picked up and thrown at enemies, as well as many other objects in the game.  Also, Omochao has many interesting things to say when he is held, thrown, destroyed, or held on a spring.  One is example is, &quot;I'm not a weapon to be thrown at enemies, you know!&quot;

I can't remember which stage but I think it works in any with Sonic or Shadow... anyhow I was trying to use my &quot;X&quot; button and the Omochao kept jumping into my arms... I jabbed away after putting him down and suddenly I started spinning in a blur... He caught fire and lay there... I did it again(held &quot;X&quot; down) and he smoked into a grey ash. I picked the ash up and threw it away... I think I killed him... sob! sob!  </TEXTAREA></TD>

